 "bull": {
  "claim": "The revenue re-acceleration from ~5% to 16.6% YoY over five quarters, with gross margin up ~210bp to 49.3%, is a durable mix shift that the Hold-rated composite underweights and that forces the street's below-spot targets upward.",
  "pillars": [
   "Growth inflection is broad, not cosmetic: revenue YoY climbed from +5.1% (2025-03) to +15.7% and +16.6% in the last two quarters, and EPS growth (+19.4%) is outpacing revenue - operating leverage, not just buybacks, is doing the work.",
   "Margin structure is improving at $4.77T scale: gross margin 49.3% in the latest quarter vs 47.2% two quarters earlier, net margin 26.6%; Profitability is the model's strongest pillar on the name at A- (10.4/12) with 26.2% return on assets.",
   "The setup punishes the sidelines: price is +25.3% over 3 months and 19% above the 200-day while the 42-analyst mean target sits 2.5% BELOW spot - each beat above the 33.8x forward-PE bar converts skeptics into forced upgrades, as the +19.4% EPS quarter just did."
  ],
  "catalysts": [
   "June-quarter print (next 1-2 months): a fourth consecutive quarter of >=15% revenue growth would confirm the inflection.",
   "Fall 2026 product cycle (H2): mix shift behind the 49.3% gross margin gets its seasonal test.",
   "EPS-revision upgrades (next 2 quarters): the B- revisions grade has room to re-rate if beats continue."
  ],
  "falsifiers": [
   "Revenue YoY decelerates below 10% for two consecutive quarters.",
   "Gross margin prints below 48% for two consecutive quarters, unwinding the mix-shift story.",
   "EPS growth falls below revenue growth for two straight quarters - the operating-leverage leg is gone."
  ]
 },
 "bear": {
  "claim": "At 39.4x trailing earnings, 2.55 PEG and a price 20.7% above the composite fair value (an -17% reversion gap), the market has pre-paid for permanence of a growth inflection the model itself only rates Hold (7.29/12, rank 58 of 201 in Technology).",
  "pillars": [
   "Valuation is the model's weakest pillar at C (4.57/12): PEG 2.55 and EV/EBITDA 29.0x price the 16.6% growth as permanent - any reversion toward the +5% prints of early 2025 leaves the multiple stranded.",
   "The composite refuses to underwrite the price: 7.29/12 (Hold), barely above the Technology sector median of 6.87 - a mid-pack score at leadership pricing, 11.4% above the quant buy point.",
   "Street exhaustion: 42 analysts with a mean target 2.5% below spot and a 2.0 recommendation score means the upgrade cycle is largely spent; what remains is momentum (+55% over 12 months, 19% above the 200-day), which cuts both ways on the first miss.",
   "Trailing optics flatter the base: the +86.4% EPS print of 2025-09 lapped a one-off depressed quarter, so trailing growth overstates the underlying earnings power the 39.4x multiple is capitalizing."
